        <h2 class="font-extrabold text-[3rem] pb-2">Everest Seller Terms and Conditions</h2>
            <h2 class="font-extrabold text-[2.2rem] pb-2">ACCOUNT SET UP</h2>
            <p class="tracking-wide leading-[1.75] text-xl font-light">
                To begin selling products on the Everest platform, merchants must first register their account. Each merchant must input their basic seller information, payment options and shipping information.
            </p>
            <p class="tracking-wide leading-[1.75] text-xl font-light">
                <span class="font-bold">Basic Seller Information: </span>This includes the company contact information. This includes the legal business name, the address associated with the legal business name and account representative contact information
            </p>
            <p class="tracking-wide leading-[1.75] text-xl font-light">
                <span class="font-bold">Payment Options: </span> Everest allows Merchants to pull their payment funds out of the Everest system. The funds in a merchant's account are visible as soon as an order comes in but are not available for withdrawal until 3 days after order has been received. After that, the funds become available for withdrawal. Funds will continue accumulating in the account until the Merchant requests them. A withdrawal of the available funds can be initiated whenever the merchant decides. Everest accepts the following payments: Visa, Mastercard, Discover card, American Express and Paypal. Paypal is offered on select products per paypal policies.
            </p>
            <p class="tracking-wide leading-[1.75] text-xl font-light">
                <span class="font-bold">Account Approval: </span>No merchant can start selling products until their account has been approved. No account is approved unless it contains all of the necessary information. Once an account is approved, the account may publish products for sale.
            </p>
            <p class="tracking-wide leading-[1.75] text-xl font-light">
                <span class="font-bold">Store Setup: </span>There is a database full of hundreds of thousands of products that merchants are likely selling, if their product is not in our database the merchant can enter it; each new product is approved by Everest before going live on the site. Merchants are responsible for keeping their in stock items up to date, unless they have entered an agreement wherein Everest will perform this service for them.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-8 border-t-3 border-ahy-blue pt-20 pb-24 ">
            <h2 class="font-extrabold text-[2.2rem] pb-2">TRANSACTION WORKFLOW</h2>
            <p class="tracking-wide leading-[1.75] text-xl font-bold">
                Everest does not sell or ship any products. Merchants use the platform as an easy state of the art e-commerce solution.
            </p>
            <p class="tracking-wide leading-[1.75] text-xl font-light">
                <span class="font-bold">Purchases: </span>When a customer finds a product to purchase, they simply add it to their cart and begin the checkout process.
            </p>
            <p class="tracking-wide leading-[1.75] text-xl font-light">
                <span class="font-bold">Shipping Information: </span> Everest is set up with flat rate shipping. When the Merchant sets up their account, they may choose the shipping methods they provide to clients. Customers will select a shipping method and merchants will fulfill it through the selected method.
            </p>
            <p class="tracking-wide leading-[1.75] text-xl font-light">
                <span class="font-bold">Order Completion: </span>When a merchant’s store has had a purchase, they will receive the order via email. They then complete the transaction via the Everest merchant portal. From there they will verify the purchase, input the shipping details, and close out the order. Each merchant on Everest is responsible for shipping the products they have listed on the website. Each merchant will handle their own product fulfillment. Everest does not touch or store any products for merchants.
            </p>
            <p class="tracking-wide leading-[1.75] text-xl font-light">
                <span class="font-bold">Communication: </span> Through Everest the customer will receive emails depicting the status of their order and will receive tracking information once their order has shipped. The customer and merchant have open lines of communication via the merchant dashboard.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-8 border-t-3 border-ahy-blue pt-20 pb-24 ">
            <h2 class="font-extrabold text-[2.2rem] pb-2">DISPUTE RESOLUTION</h2>
            <p class="tracking-wide leading-[1.75] text-xl font-light">
            Each merchant is responsible for handling all refund, dispute, or chargeback inquiries. However, Everest will assist the merchant in fighting chargebacks, refunds and disputes. Everest representatives will work with both the merchant and the customer to resolve the issue in a timely manner.
            </p>
            <p class="tracking-wide leading-[1.75] text-xl font-light">
                <span class="font-bold">Refund policy: </span>After a merchant has agreed and authorized a refund to the customer, the merchant has several options to consider. The merchant can wait until they receive the item back from the customer before issuing the refund. If the product is sent back damaged or in any condition that is not acceptable to the merchant, the merchant may issue a partial refund. Sometimes a customer will send back an item that they do not want. As long as the item sold was the item described, the merchant can issue a refund and not the shipping costs.
            </p>
            <p class="tracking-wide leading-[1.75] text-xl font-light">
                <span class="font-bold">Chargeback policy: </span> The merchant will be provided with the chargeback information. Once received, they must provide Everest with proof of delivery, date the order was shipped, tracking number, and verified shipping address. If a merchant does not follow the steps to rectify the charge back, Everest will deduct the chargeback amount from their sellers account. Everest will assist the merchant in all chargeback disputes as long as the chargeback was issued due to “unauthorized transaction”
            </p>
            <p class="tracking-wide leading-[1.75] text-xl font-light">
                <span class="font-bold">Rules and Regulations: </span>By using the Everest platform, all Merchants agree to abide by all local, state, and federal laws, rules, and regulations pertaining to their products. Everest waives all responsibilities in this matter.
            </p>
            <p class="tracking-wide leading-[1.75] text-xl font-light">
                <span class="font-bold">Disputes: </span>By using the Everest platform, all Merchants agree to abide by any dispute resolution decisions handed down by Everest or a third party conflict resolution professional.
            </p>
            <p class="tracking-wide leading-[1.75] text-xl font-light">
                <span class="font-bold">Purchases: </span>By using the Everest platform, all Merchants agree to, to the best of their ability, keep their store stock information up to date, and to quickly and correctly ship any purchases made through the platform.
            </p>
            <p class="tracking-wide leading-[1.75] text-xl font-light">
                <span class="font-bold">Payouts: </span>By using the Everest platform, all Merchants agree that they will not receive funds for any transaction until 3 days after the order has been verified to be received by the consumer.
            </p>
            <p class="tracking-wide leading-[1.75] text-xl font-light">
                <span class="font-bold">Fees: </span> By using the Everest platform, all Merchants agree to pay a 9% fee on all transactions.
            </p>
